    Oh, yeah, that's right.     

16:10.369 --> 16:13.203
      I won't sing anymore      
      until after we eat.       

16:21.346 --> 16:23.046
Who's bringing the pizza?       

16:23.048 --> 16:25.182
        A couple of friends     
         of mine down the block.

16:25.184 --> 16:26.684
            I wonder what's     
            taking them so long.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.185
                    It's really 
                getting late.   

16:28.187 --> 16:29.820
I wonder                        
how Michael is.                 

16:29.822 --> 16:32.356
 I think I'm going to call him  
    over at Lionel's and...     

16:32.358 --> 16:34.391
                 Gloria,        
                 don't you dare.

16:34.393 --> 16:36.393
He walked out on you, remember? 

16:36.395 --> 16:37.962
     Make him come to you.      

16:37.964 --> 16:39.663
    But what if he doesn't?     

16:39.665 --> 16:43.033
 Oh, Gloria, I'm sure he will.  

16:43.035 --> 16:44.969
 It's just like in the movies.  

16:44.971 --> 16:48.038
        The husband always ran  
        after the wife,         

16:48.040 --> 16:52.142
and he said, "Please come back,"
    and the wife always did.    

16:52.144 --> 16:55.613
      Like William Powell       
        and Myrna Loy...        

16:55.615 --> 16:57.848
Cary Grant and Irene Dunne...   

16:57.850 --> 16:59.850
Humphrey Bogart and Bette Davis?

16:59.852 --> 17:01.519
             Yeah.              

17:01.521 --> 17:05.422
Only you were never too sure    
        about Bette Davis.      

17:08.527 --> 17:10.994
  Sometimes, she'd come back,   

17:10.997 --> 17:14.196
  but sometimes, she'd just die.

17:17.502 --> 17:19.869
        Oh, pizza!              

17:19.872 --> 17:21.137
         Hi, everybody.         

17:21.140 --> 17:22.472
              Oh, Mrs. Bunker,  

17:22.473 --> 17:23.807
            this is Betty Sue,  
            and Joanie.         

